[Could you provide more description on this issue?, [~daryn], please have a look., we will apply patch to fix this bug later, I'll take a look.  We've been running with async edit logs for 3 years so I'm really surprised we haven't encountered the problem.  The multi-edit roll did require very special attention.

What specific release encountered this problem?  Was it a stock community release or vendor release?, It is indeed possible.  Rolling with a full edit queue will deadlock., Almost have a very small fix ready, just making sure there is a tight test case that specifically exercises the code paths.  Instead of current tests that just spin for awhile and assume everything worked..., Unit testing was virtually unable to reproduce the issue. Determined main issue is caused by token expiration not acquiring the fsn lock while edit logging., sure we alread found expire token is default hourly put edit to asyqueue without acquire editlog lock, let me upload the patch, but i have not write unit test,  we already apply it in our prod env., The fix is much simpler. Top priority, posted other patches to address main cause, trying to make sure unit test for my patch for this Jira is airtight to prove race is closed. Will post tomorrow morning., Finally got back to this.  Basic issue is a synchronized caller (ie. log rolling) must use wait() to relinquish the monitor so the async thread has a chance to drain the full queue.  Non-synchronized caller can just put.

